<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880421-0010 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Southern California Gas </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RD SC PET </CO><IN> LNG </IN><TEXT>   Southern California Gas Co., Los Angeles, said it signed a 20-year contract valued at more than $260 million to transport natural gas for a Royal Dutch/Shell Group unit.    Southern California Gas, a unit of Los Angeles-based Pacific Enterprises, will transport natural gas to Shell Western Eandamp;P's oil recovery operations in central and southern California. The contract, which must be approved by the California Public Utilities Commission, provides for the transporation of as much as 250 million cubic feet of gas a day. </TEXT></DOC>